(1208, 573, 'introduction', 'The Green Gravel Comedy fest will be a weekend of curated comedy madness running from February 27-28, 2015. Boasting live stand-up, improv, podcast and sketch material, Iowa City will be bustling with fans and creators alike. We look forward to facilitating a platform for comedy creators to share their work while networking, partying and influencing each other in ways previously unimaginable!\r\n\r\nThere are a number of venues that showcase comedy in Iowa - from bars to comedy clubs to talent shows. Our goal is to give a voice to the performers that have yearned to grace those stages as much as those who have been prominently featured there. We welcome diverse submissions in the realm of stand-up, podcasts and one-man-show comedy! This is your chance to showcase your very finest work! Nothing is too weird. This is your time. We''ll be particularly on the lookout for talent within the Hawkeye state.'),
(1209, 573, '_introduction', 'field_547dd9670d19a'),
(1210, 573, 'criteria', '<b>Please send the following to Submissions@</b><b>GreenGravelComedyFest.com:</b>\r\n\r\nName, City/State, Email, Synopsis (if a one-person show or podcast) Video Link, Website or Credits.\r\n\r\nSubmission Fees:\r\n\r\n$15 - Iowa Stand-up Comedians (Must provide verification of Iowa residency or address. This can be in the form of a past link to your work in Iowa, a cell pic of one of your utility bills, or yr mom calling us.) (Please dont have yr mom call us.)\r\n\r\n$20 - Podcast Submissions, One-man/woman Shows, Musical Comedy Acts\r\n\r\n$25 - Out-of-State Stand-up Comedians\r\n\r\nSubmission Fees should be sent to the same email via PayPal. Submissions that are not accompanied by the submission fee will not be considered.\r\n\r\nAll submissions are due by midnight on Monday, January 5th. No submissions will be accepted after this time and any submission fees from late entrants will be returned.\r\n\r\n*Note: We will be premiering an outreach program for Green Gravel performers to come out to LA to showcase work in front of industry professionals in 2015. Eligibility for this program will be available exclusively to performers who have been previously accepted to perform at Green Gravel functions.\r\n\r\nGG 2015 is already slated to feature some of Iowa''s great indie/alt comedy shows/performers: JANICE, Little Village Comedy Hour, Paperback Rhino and more! We cant wait for you to join them and look forward to seeing your best stuff!\r\n\r\n-The Green Gravel Team'),
